cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.HC 

This paper discusses the application of theories about the Human Visual System to Adversarial AI, which involves image processing and machine learning. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). Additionally, the paper involves the use of complex models to better approximate the HVS, which suggests a focus on AI and machine learning, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence and Machine Learning) another likely category. The paper also discusses the effectiveness of different models, which suggests a focus on optimization and performance, making cs.LG (Learning) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) possible categories. Finally, the paper discusses the HVS, which suggests a focus on human-computer interaction, making cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) a possible category as well.
